-- Societe Generale Is Doubling M&A Banker Headcount Worldwide, Peretie Says
-- Fabio Benedetti-Valentini
-- 2010-06-15T17:08:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/societe-generale-is-doubling-m-a-banker-headcount-worldwide-peretie-says.html

          
          
             Societe Generale SA  is doubling its
mergers and acquisitions headcount worldwide, said  Michel Peretie , the head of the corporate and investment bank.  
 As part of the expansion, Societe Generale is hiring 25
senior M&A bankers between 2009 and 2010, Peretie told investors
in Paris today. The bank set a profit target for the corporate
and investment bank of between 2.3 billion euros ($2.8 billion)
and 2.8 billion euros in 2012.  
 At its debt business, Societe Generale plans to hire 200
front-office staff by 2012 to expand its origination and
distribution of fixed-income products in U.S. dollars and
pounds, Peretie said.  
 Overall, Societe Generaleâ€™s corporate- and investment-
banking unit aims to increase front-office staff by 1,200 people
by 2012, Peretie said.  
